   <narrative xml:lang="EN">El Nino emergency relief in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peru is currently threaten by the most heavy rains in the last two decades. The unusual heavy rains have caused the worst floods, landslide and overflowing rivers, causing deaths, massive destruction of houses, and an increasing risk for mosquito-related diseases. Care Peru&apos;s immediate response is to provide health and water kits to families in the severely affected areas in the north of the country. We have set a target to distribute 8,000 family health and water kits to impact 40,000 people.</narrative>
  </description>
